04/01/2008
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- One policeman was killed and two others were injured when gunmen opened fire on their vehicle with a machinegun on Thursday (January 3rd).
The officers, members of a police special forces unit, were ambushed in their all-terrain vehicle on the exit ramp of the Skopje-Veles highway, near the capital.
The assailants' vehicle was later found abandoned in the ethnic Albanian village of Aracinovo, outside Skopje.
No arrests have been made.
This was the latest in a series of incidents involving police.
Four alleged gangsters died in a gunfight with the police on November 7th.
(Dnevnik - 04/01/08;
DPA, Xinhua, Makfax, MIA, A1, AP - 03/01/08)
